Here are both approaches:

**1. Register the route in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

**2. Navigate from `ProductListPage` (or its ViewModel):**

```csharp
// Approach A — string ID via query string
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive both in one ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter arrives as a string value
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load the full product from a service using the ID
        }

        // Approach B — complex object arrives as-is, just cast it
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?productId=...`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| Data type | Strings only | Any object |
| Serialization | Value is URL-encoded | No serialization, passed by reference |
| Back-navigation | Survives URI reconstruction | Not available on back-nav |
| Use when | You have a simple ID/key | You already have the object in memory |

**Important:** Always `await` `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions. And make sure the ViewModel is set as the page's `BindingContext` so Shell can find the `IQueryAttributable` implementation.
